<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 2:25PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Gallatin County through 300 PM MDT...
At 224 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bozeman, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 45 mph and occasional lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Bozeman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
